description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Band 5 and 6 Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employer: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: South West Division Hampshire - SHFT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Various – New Forest and Southampton areas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Dependent on Banding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type: Both permanent and fixed term contracts available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working pattern:  Variable - Part / Full time considered – There may be some weekend working in the future&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Scheme: Agenda for change&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Band: 5 or 6 dependent on skills and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Group: Allied Health Professionals&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: TBC – provisionally Tuesday 24th November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for both Junior and Senior Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists to join our dynamic and supportive Therapy Teams across the South West Division. The areas we support as part of SHFT South West Division are areas of the New Forest such as Lymington, Totton and Fordingbridge areas and the surrounding areas of Southampton such as Romsey, Chandlers Ford and Eastleigh Southern Parishes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are currently recruiting to additional posts division wide to support the delivery of a Discharge to Assess (D2A) model of care. This is an exciting time to join our services as we transition into delivering care in an innovative way to meet the needs of our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The posts advertised are to work as part of our Integrated Care Services as therapists working within the Integrated / One Team model of care, with community services, primary care and the wider MDT working closely together to provide exemplary care to local populations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The type of work we do in the community varies from urgent response to prevent hospital admissions, supporting patients on discharge from hospital and devising rehabilitation and or management programmes for patients with a wide variety of long term conditions. There may also be opportunities to work with our services that provide inpatient care to medical and rehabilitation beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We are looking for applicants who are keen to develop, able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, be team players and be able to prioritise their workloads with a patient focused approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We would welcome applications from forward thinking and flexible OTs and Physiotherapists with a real passion and interest for community working, rehabilitation and the wider systems we work within.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; You will need to be a qualified HCPC registered OT or Physiotherapist with current driving licence and access to a car for work purposes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We have both substantive and fixed term contracts available for the right candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; To see a job description specific to your relevant profession and banding please contact us as below and we would be happy to share these with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; Full Time / Part Time hours considered&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To see a profession or banding specific job description or to discuss these opportunities further please contact Jamie Hawthorn Integrated Clinical Lead Physiotherapist via email at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jamie.hawthorn@southernhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Happy to talk flexible working&lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; all requests for flexible and part time working will be considered.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
